ðŸ¤” Q. Write a program to search for a number x in this tuple using while loop.
      (1, 4, 9, 16, 25, 36, 49, 64, 81, 100) - Linear Search

# Code

No = int(input("Enter Number = "))

Tuple = (1, 4, 9, 16, 25, 36, 49, 64, 81, 100, 25)
Index = 0

while Index < len(Tuple):

  if (Tuple[Index] == No):
    print("Number found in Tuple at Index = ", Index)
  else:
    print("Finding")

  Index += 1


- O/P.:
Enter Number = 25
Finding
Finding
Finding
Finding
Number found in Tuple at Index = 4
Finding
Finding
Finding
Finding
Finding
Number found in Tuple at Index = 10




ðŸ¤” Q. Write a program to search for a number x in this tuple using for loop.
      (1, 4, 9, 16, 25, 36, 49, 64, 81, 100, 25)

# Code

Number = int(input("Enter Number = "))

Tuple = (1, 4, 9, 16, 25, 36, 49, 64, 81, 100, 25)
Index = 0

for x in Tuple:

  if (x == Number):
    print("Number found in Tuple at Index = ", Index)
  Index += 1


- O/P.:
Enter Number = 25
Number found in Tuple at Index = 4
Number found in Tuple at Index = 10




ðŸ¤” Q. Write a program to find in which line of the file does any input word occur first.

# Code

f = open("Practice.txt", "r")
print(f.read())

Word = input("Enter word to find = ")
Data = True
LineNo = 1

with open("Practice.txt", "r") as f:

    while Data:
        Data = f.readline()

        if Word in Data:
            print(f"\"{Word}\" word found at line no. = ", LineNo)
            break
        
        LineNo += 1

    else:
        print("Word not Found")


- O/P.:
Hi Everyone !!!
We are learning Python.
Subtopic is "File Handling in Python".
In this we will study Open, Close, Operate and Delete Methods.

Enter word to find = Python
"Python" word found at line no. = 2
